ce:section.ce:para:
Interestingly, SE45 displayed greater sensitivity to parameter variations compared to SE19, likely due to its lower particle size ratio (
                           λ
                        ), making it more responsive to changes in friction and mechanical properties. This differential sensitivity between SE45 and SE19 highlights the importance of particle size distribution in determining the material’s packing behavior and overall performance, particularly concerning porosity.
